reviews.review_text: Tip of The Cap (of the Skull) Hats Off To Eddie, Rob & Charlie. This Was A Splendid Run After the East Coast Spring Jaunt and Before The Garcia Bands Endeavors Hear & About In June. The Band was Engaging Night After Night. With Splendid Playing and Strong Shows Throughout. This'n for Example. The Energy Continued Thru The JGB Tour with Billy Joining In On Drums and Several Shows Booked With Bobby & The Midnites. The Vista Cruiser was Out and Fine Tuned and Sheer Momentum Took 'em Far Into Th Fall and On Into The Holly Days. !982, A Very Fine Year... {Now To Our Hosts Here at IA. Give It Up Folks, In Dollars and Cents. Give 'em Sumpthin'.}  The Sound On This On The Other Hand Is Nothing Less Than Professional Remastering Done By Jeff Norman & The Likes Over There At "WARNER BROTHERS." Charlie, Rob and Eddie, We Love You Three, And Jeff You Too. (n' almost every body over there at Warner Bros.)  So When Those First Bars Of Jack Straw Come Rumblin Out . Offer Up A Positive Vibe, Prayer, Good Wishes To Eddie Claridge, Rob Eaton & The Notorius Charlie Miller. I GiveItAFiveCuzICanDanceT'wit
